      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JINDALEA JACK (8) finished fourth when resuming at Charlton two starts back then was highly competitive at his latest appearance at Maryborough, beaten only 1.7 metres into third after being close to the pace throughout. No harm in drawing here with the sprint lane to rely upon. Building in fitness and is good enough to win a race of this calibre. ELIZAJANE (3) clocked in third three back at Shepparton and hasn't been far from the placings since. Draws well and placed the only time she attempted this circuit and distance. MAURLEN GRACE (4) is still a maiden but should be ready to peak now after finishing second at Ballarat a week ago and has more upside than many of these. HIGHVIEW HAMMER (6) can feature if he shows the form that saw him score last month at Maryborough.",
